description: TEHRAN - The Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) on Wednesday blamed Israel for an attack that killed Hamas political chief Ismail Haniyeh last week in Tehran, Iran’s capital.

description: TEHRAN – Mobina Nematzadeh of Iran claimed a bronze medal in the women's 49kg taekwondo played out inside Paris' spectacular Grand Palais on Wednesday.
title: Iran’s Nematzadeh grabs bronze in taekwondo: 2024 Paris

description: TEHRAN – Greco-Roman wrestler Mohammadhadi Saravi won a gold medal in the 2024 Olympic Games.

description: TEHRAN-The Iranian short film “Abraham” co-directed by Elnaz Ghaderpour and Reza Gamini is present at the 20th HollyShorts Film Festival which kicks off on August 8 in California, the U.S.
title: Iranian short film “Abraham” competes in 20th HollyShorts Film Festival

description: TEHRAN– Iran’s Foreign Ministry has urged the Afghan caretaker government to publicly announce the findings of its investigations into the assassination of Iranian diplomats and a reporter in Mazar-e Sharif on August 8, 1998, and to ensure that those responsible are held accountable.
title: Tehran demands justice for 1998 killing of Iranian reporter and diplomats in Afghanistan

description: TEHRAN- Iran’s air defense system in the eastern region has been upgraded with new radars and missile interceptors, as announced during a ceremony attended by the chief commander of Iran’s Army Air Defense Force.
title: Iran bolsters air defenses with new radar systems: official

description: TEHRAN- Iran’s cultural attaché in Iraq and the Iraqi director general of the Department of Cultural Relations have announced the establishment of a joint cultural committee between the two nations.
title: Iran, Iraq form joint committee to strengthen cultural ties

description: TEHRAN – The Islamic Republic of Iran has firmly denied any involvement with a Pakistani national, who has reportedly been arrested in the United States and accused of orchestrating a foiled plot to assassinate prominent U.S. politicians.
title: Tehran denies involvement in alleged plot to assassinate U.S. politicians

description: TEHRAN – Iran's acting foreign minister, Ali Baqeri Kani, has issued a stern warning against Israel's destabilizing activities in the West Asia region, vowing that the Islamic Republic will not permit Israel to manipulate regional stability and security for its own illegitimate objectives.

description: TEHRAN– The chief commander of the Iranian Army, Major General Abdolrahim Mousavi, held talks with the visiting Commander of Air Force and Air Defense of the Republic of Belarus, Major General Andrey Lukyanovich, in a meeting attended by several other high-ranking generals in Tehran.
title: Iran-Belarus discuss international threats in high-ranking military meeting

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Acting Foreign Minister has condemned the U.S. for insulating Israel against punitive measures by the Security Council, adding that in the absence of any appropriate action by the UN body, Iran has no option but to exercise its inherent right to legitimate defense against the regime’s aggressions.

description: TEHRAN – Mashhad has witnessed a substantial boost in medical tourism, welcoming thousands of international patients in the first quarter of this Persian year (started on March 20).

description: TEHRAN – In a move to enhance bilateral relations between Iran and Tajikistan, a visa-waiver program will be implemented between the two nations starting Saturday, August 10.

description: TEHRAN – Located in the heart of Isfahan, the ancient city that graces the crossroads of Iran’s north-south and east-west routes, Naqsh-e Jahan is jewel of the Safavid era (1501-1736).

description: TEHRAN - Iran secured the third-place position in the CAVA Women’s Volleyball Nations League, defeating Sri Lanka in straight sets (25-22, 28-26, 25-17).
title: Iran come third in CAVA Women’s Volleyball Nations League

description: TEHRAN - Electricity consumption in Iran has increased by 6,000 megawatts (MW) in the current Iranian year (started on March 20) compared to the previous year, Head of Iran's Power Generation, Distribution, and Transmission Company (known as Tavanir) Mostafa Rajabi Mashhadi said.
title: Electricity consumption in Iran rises 6,000 MW

description: TEHRAN – Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (ICCIMA) hosted a conference on new economic innovations in Iran’s economic sector on Wednesday, the ICCIMA portal reported.
title: ICCIMA hosts conference on innovative ways to develop Iran’s economy

description: TEHRAN – The Ambassador of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) in Tehran has said over 122,000 Iranian business persons are currently working in the UAE, IRNA reported.
title: Over 122,000 Iranian businesspersons active in UAE markets: envoy

description: TEHRAN – Based on Iran’s seventh National Development Plan (2023-2027) the country plans to develop the cultivation of medical herbs in 300,000 hectares of natural landscapes, an official with Iran’s Natural Resources and Watershed Management Organization said.
title: Iran to cultivate medical herbs in 300,000 hectares of lands

description: TEHRAN - Transit of commodities through Iran reached 16.34 million tons during the previous Iranian calendar year (ended on March 19), which is a new record high, according to an official with the country’s Transport and Urban Development Ministry.

description: TEHRAN- The value of non-oil export from Golestan province, in the northeast of Iran, rose 60 percent during the first four months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-July 21), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, a provincial official announced.
title: Export from Golestan province rises 60% in 4 months on year

description: TEHRAN – The loading and unloading of goods in Amir-Abad port, in the northern Mazandaran province, increased by 19 percent during the first four months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-July 21), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, a local official announced.
title: Loading, unloading of goods in Amir-Abad port up 19% in 4 months on year

description: A massive fire in the oak forests of Marivan, west of the country, was extinguished after 48 hours of continuous efforts by the environmental protection forces and local people.
title: Wildfire in oak forests contained

description: TEHRAN –The expansion of lands for the cultivation of medicinal plants by 300,000 hectares is one of the set goals in the seventh five-year national development plan (2023 – 2027).
title: Expanding cultivation of medicinal plants by 2027 on agenda

description: TEHRAN –The health ministry has highlighted the significance of getting vaccinated for Arbaeen pilgrims, particularly those who are under 15 years of age, to prevent illness or deaths caused by measles.
title: Health ministry underscores measles vaccination for Arbaeen pilgrims

description: TEHRAN – New images of the long-tailed nesokia (Nesokia bunnii), one of the rarest and endangered rodents of the world, were recorded in Hour al-Azim wetland on Tuesday.
title: Rare long-tailed nesokia seen in Hour al-Azim wetland
